          <source>The member typedef type names the same type as <ph id="ph1">`remove_reference&lt;T&gt;::type*`</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Because it is invalid to make a pointer from a reference, <ph id="ph1">`add_pointer`</ph> removes the reference, if any, from the specified type before it makes a pointer-to-type.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Consequently, you can use a type with <ph id="ph1">`add_pointer`</ph> without being concerned about whether the type is a reference.</source>
